The pair surprised many, including their friend Oskido, when they decided to legally register their union at their home on Thursday evening.Luckily for us, Oskido was present at the ceremony and recorded a short video after the ceremony.A video posted by oskidoibelieve (@oskidoibelieve) on Jan 5, 2017 at 11:27am PSTA video posted by oskidoibelieve (@oskidoibelieve) on Jan 5, 2017 at 11:27am PSTIt wasn't a very formal affair, with Black Coffee wearing a smart shirt and Enhle wearing a cream suit with a veil on her head.Oskido couldn't help but gush over the pair, wishing them a happy union."I witness a union of two beautiful spirits. May your hearts be always near both in good and bad times, may you always hold on to each other with trust and faith. Wishing you a blissfully married life! You are now one. Congrats," he wrote.The pair will celebrate their union with a white wedding at Sun City on Sunday January 8.TshisaLIVE understands that the wedding has been planned by actress-turned-wedding planner Sophie Ndaba and security is expected to be tight for the event.The couple got engaged in 2010 and in 2011 had a traditional wedding in Soweto.They have two children together. 